Date: Sat, 20 May 2000 16:37:22 -0400
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE report, 19 May 2000

Serological surveillance was completed on 11 May 2000, with no evidence of
infected animals since 9 Apr 2000 (see Disease Information, 13 [15, 61,
dated 21 Apr 2000), except the two animals mentioned below.
New outbreak: Location Honbetsu-cho, Hokkaido Prefecture
Description of affected population in the new outbreak: fattening cattle on
1 farm.
Total number of animals in the new outbreak:
species bovine
susceptible 705
cases 2* [no clinical signs but positive laboratory results on PCR and
ELISA - Mod.PC
deaths 0
destroyed 705
slaughtered 0
*Diagnostic tests used: RT-PCR(1), ELISA(2) for antibody detection.
Control measures during reporting period:
- all cattle kept in the farm were destroyed and the farm was disinfected;
- movement control of potentially contaminated animals and materials is
carried out within a 10-km radius of the infected farm;
- intensive surveillance has been taking place in the 10-km-radius movement
control area.
